<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-13T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4949: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-13T17:00:00-04:00">August 13, 1936—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>337. Your 508, August 4, 9 a.m. The Paris Embassy reports that the
                                matter was taken up with the Foreign Office on August 8 and that the
                                Foreign Office has now replied that they are at a loss to understand
                                why the shipment was held up and that the Ministry of Colonies has
                                been requested to telegraph the necessary instructions to the
                                Governor of French Somaliland for the forwarding of the shipment to
                                you.</p>
                            <p>Please keep the Department promptly informed of developments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>